description:
&lt;p&gt;Chief Clinical Physiologist Team Leader (Invasive Cardiology including Electrophysiology)&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;An exciting opportunity has arisen for a highly motivated and enthusiastic individual&lt;br /&gt;to join our busy and dynamic cardiac physiology team at The Newcastle upon Tyne&lt;br /&gt;Hospitals NHS Foundation Trust.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;br /&gt;We are currently seeking a Chief Cardiac Physiologist to join our friendly but&lt;br /&gt;dedicated team. The post will be predominantly based in the Cardiac Cath Lab&lt;br /&gt;focusing mainly on electrophysiology and coordinating junior staff in all aspects of&lt;br /&gt;invasive service. This post would suit an individual looking to enhance their&lt;br /&gt;knowledge and develop specialist electrophysiology/invasive skills. Our&lt;br /&gt;internationally renowned Cardiothoracic Directorate provides secondary and tertiary&lt;br /&gt;Cardiac and transplantation services to the North of England and beyond. The&lt;br /&gt;successful applicant will therefore be working at the cutting edge of&lt;br /&gt;Electrophysiology within this setting. Candidates should have experience working&lt;br /&gt;independently within EP and proficient in the use of 3D mapping.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;br /&gt;The post holder will be expected to work alongside the Professional Lead Cardiac&lt;br /&gt;Physiologist and deputise in planning meetings, able to perform appraisals for&lt;br /&gt;physiology staff working in Invasive areas and have full oversight of E-rostering.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;br /&gt;Continued professional and personal development is actively encouraged and&lt;br /&gt;successful candidates will be given opportunities and will be supported to develop&lt;br /&gt;their postgraduate skills.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;br /&gt;The post holder is required to participate in the electrophysiology on-call rota ,&lt;br /&gt;providing 24 hour emergency service cover. Applicants must possess BSc (Hons) in&lt;br /&gt;Cardiac Physiology or equivalent, BHRS and registration with RCCP or equivalent is&lt;br /&gt;essential.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Full time 37 Hours 30 Minutes/Week&lt;/p&gt;
